= Introduction =
{{project_name_short}} {{cli}} is normally recommended for advanced users only. However, it is possible to reduce the RAM and VRAM (video RAM) assignment of {{project_name_gateway_short}} without requiring any other configuration changes such as package de-installation or configuration file modifications.

It is important to note that more RAM is required for upgrades.

{{project_name_gateway_long}} can function with as little as 256 MB RAM, resource-intensive operations like upgrades can cause the virtual machine to freeze. <ref name=kernel-upgrade>
For instance, kernel package upgrades that rebuild the initrd.
</ref>

Assigning less than 512 MB RAM to a {{project_name_long}} VM will result in [[RAM_Adjusted_Desktop_Starter|RAM Adjusted Desktop Starter]] launching the {{cli}} only, without Xfce {{gui}}.

Users with 4 GB or less RAM can temporarily assign 256 MB RAM to {{project_name_gateway_long}}. This is sufficient for the normal operation of {{project_name_gateway_long}} serving {{project_name_workstation_long}}. This process is described in detail below.

